metadata.name: acl
metadata.summary: Utilities for managing POSIX Access Control Lists
metadata.description: ACL allows you to provide different levels of access to files and folders for different users.

issue.summary: The (1) setfacl and (2) getfacl commands in XFS acl 2.2.47, when running in recursive (-R) mode, follow symbolic links even when the --physical (aka -P) or -L option is specified, which might allow local users to modify the ACL for arbitrary files or directories via a symlink attack.
